President Obama has nominated Mark Ericks, Joseph P. Faughnan, Donald Martin O'Keefe, H. Michael Oglesby, Kenneth Runde, and Charles T. Weeks II to serve as U.S. Marshals. These individuals have demonstrated a strong commitment to justice throughout their careers. Mark Ericks has a background in law enforcement and currently serves in the Washington State House of Representatives. Joseph P. Faughnan is the Chief of Police for the Town of Clinton, Connecticut. Donald Martin O'Keefe is the Chief of Police for Half Moon Bay, California. H. Michael Oglesby is the Sheriff and Collector for Polk County, Arkansas. Kenneth Runde is the Sheriff of Dubuque County, Iowa. Charles T. Weeks II is a Major with the Oklahoma Highway Patrol.